1
00:01:34,880 --> 00:01:39,990
[This Thriving Land]

2
00:01:40,310 --> 00:01:42,940
[Episode 15]

3
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:53,830
Sister-in-law,

4
00:01:53,860 --> 00:01:55,200
I still want to talk to you.

5
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,200
I don't have time.

6
00:01:56,350 --> 00:01:58,350
Sister-in-law, where are you going?

7
00:01:58,350 --> 00:01:59,950
I'm going to the Goddess Temple,

8
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:01,000
to fulfill my vow,

9
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:04,090
thanking Her
for granting the Fei family an heir.

10
00:02:04,090 --> 00:02:05,510
And to pray for blessings for you, Susu,

11
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:07,760
and the baby in Susu's belly. Happy now?

12
00:02:07,950 --> 00:02:09,160
Sister-in-law, must you go now?

13
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:11,520
Fulfilling a vow
doesn't need to be this urgent.

14
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:12,540
But I promised to do it today—

15
00:02:12,540 --> 00:02:13,360
it has to be today.

16
00:02:13,360 --> 00:02:14,320
Sister-in-law!

17
00:02:14,910 --> 00:02:16,400
I heard everything from inside!

18
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,730
You're going to the Goddess Temple, right?

19
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:19,170
I love going there!

20
00:02:19,210 --> 00:02:21,100
During the New Year temple fair,
Xiuxiu just took me there!

21
00:02:21,100 --> 00:02:22,360
You're still carrying a child!

22
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,930
That mountain road is so bumpy—

23
00:02:23,930 --> 00:02:25,910
what if you get jostled around
in the carriage?

24
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:27,310
You'll worry me to death!

25
00:02:27,610 --> 00:02:29,840
Be good and rest at home, alright?

26
00:02:29,870 --> 00:02:31,400
I'll bring you back treats.

27
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:33,190
Sister-in-law...

28
00:02:33,190 --> 00:02:33,590
You—

29
00:02:33,810 --> 00:02:35,700
stay home and take good care of Susu.

30
00:02:35,700 --> 00:02:36,230
Let's go.

31
00:02:44,590 --> 00:02:45,280
Susu,

32
00:02:45,530 --> 00:02:46,960
you rest well inside, alright?

33
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,220
I'm going out for a bit.

34
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,590
Why won't they take me
to the Temple of the Goddess?

35
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:54,390
So unfair!

36
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:58,250
Everyone's out enjoying
this lovely weather...

37
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:00,850
Might as well suffocate me in here!

38
00:03:14,620 --> 00:03:16,500
Let out the string!

39
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:17,590
Hurry up, hurry up!

40
00:03:17,590 --> 00:03:18,400
It's flying!

41
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,430
Wait for me!

42
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:20,770
Stop grabbing it!

43
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:21,680
Wait—!

44
00:03:21,710 --> 00:03:23,079
Spring's really in the air—

45
00:03:23,079 --> 00:03:24,910
even the kids are flying kites now.

46
00:03:24,910 --> 00:03:26,079
If I had a son,

47
00:03:26,220 --> 00:03:28,300
I'd make him a soaring eagle kite!

48
00:03:29,050 --> 00:03:30,360
Enough daydreaming.

49
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,590
Back to work.

50
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:33,230
Zhuzi, Zhuzi's wife,

51
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:34,829
busy with work, I see.

52
00:03:35,870 --> 00:03:37,030
I'd like to have a word with you.

53
00:03:37,030 --> 00:03:37,360
Huh?

54
00:03:37,680 --> 00:03:38,680
Chat with us?

55
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:40,320
Yeah, just a little chat.

56
00:03:41,240 --> 00:03:42,520
But we're working—

57
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:44,990
you'll end up with mud all over your feet!

58
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:46,090
It doesn't matter.

59
00:03:46,390 --> 00:03:48,110
I just… wanted to talk with you.

60
00:03:48,110 --> 00:03:49,960
About something you'd care to hear.

61
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,800
What topic would we care about?

62
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:54,840
Besides farming and filling our bellies,

63
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,900
what else is there?

64
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:57,150
he Farmers' Association—

65
00:03:57,150 --> 00:03:59,150
what do you think about it?

66
00:03:59,760 --> 00:04:00,320
And...

67
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:02,120
what about
the Northern Expedition Army's march?

68
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:04,740
They helped us
establish associations along the way,

69
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:07,120
fight for lower rents
and reduced interest rates,

70
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:09,940
and promote permanent tenancy rights.
Any thoughts on this?

71
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:10,650
Mr. Fei,

72
00:04:11,400 --> 00:04:12,650
Sure, I've heard things

73
00:04:12,650 --> 00:04:14,630
about those Farmers' Associations.

74
00:04:14,630 --> 00:04:15,430
But look at us—

75
00:04:16,190 --> 00:04:17,100
we're just renting a few poor acres

76
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:18,940
from Li Junyi.

77
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:21,320
After rent's paid,
we barely keep ourselves fed.

78
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,120
On top of that,

79
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,870
there's also Zhang Zongchang?

80
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:25,110
Tax after tax—

81
00:04:25,870 --> 00:04:27,640
they've skinned us near to death.

82
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:28,980
What you're talking about...

83
00:04:28,980 --> 00:04:30,760
doesn't mean much
to folks like us.

84
00:04:30,760 --> 00:04:33,460
We only believe
what these eyes can see.

85
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:35,340
What we can't see? We don't trust.

86
00:04:35,430 --> 00:04:35,890
Move it!

87
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,960
Zhuzi, that's where you're wrong!

88
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:40,760
Just because something's unseen,

89
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:42,650
doesn't mean it can't succeed.

90
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:45,740
Supporting the Farmers' Association
means fighting for our own welfare—

91
00:04:45,740 --> 00:04:47,770
this is earth-shaking change

92
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,530
for all us farmers!

93
00:04:49,909 --> 00:04:52,830
With reduced rents and interest cuts,

94
00:04:52,850 --> 00:04:54,240
with permanent tenancy rights,

95
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,600
we'll have better lives.

96
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,040
This is where we find real hope
for the future. Don't you agree?

97
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:58,920
Mr. Fei.

98
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:01,190
All this talk of yours,

99
00:05:01,630 --> 00:05:03,120
supposedly for the benefit

100
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:05,160
of us farmers—

101
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:06,030
Exactly.

102
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:10,910
Then I really don't get it.

103
00:05:12,750 --> 00:05:13,790
You are a young master

104
00:05:13,790 --> 00:05:15,350
from a landlord family.

105
00:05:16,530 --> 00:05:18,270
That lower rents, lower interest,

106
00:05:18,270 --> 00:05:19,270
even permanent tenancy…

107
00:05:19,270 --> 00:05:20,720
wouldn't all that hurt you?

108
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:22,360
Now, if someone else said it,

109
00:05:22,950 --> 00:05:24,040
maybe I'd listen.

110
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:27,640
But coming from you?
Just feels… off.

111
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:30,350
I'm not even your family's tenant,

112
00:05:30,350 --> 00:05:31,350
but shouldn't you at least

113
00:05:31,350 --> 00:05:33,230
ask your sister-in-law first?

114
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:35,080
If she and the other landlords

115
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:35,909
actually agreed to cut rents and taxes
for farmers—
So just… drop it.

116
00:05:35,909 --> 00:05:38,880
even permanent land rights—

117
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,030
we'd be overjpyed!

118
00:05:41,030 --> 00:05:42,909
You don't have to
go door-to-door preaching.

119
00:05:42,909 --> 00:05:44,150
Let's... drop it here for now.

120
00:05:44,150 --> 00:05:45,270
Alright, let's go.

121
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,140
Come on.

122
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:47,710
Yes,

123
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:49,850
you're absolutely right.

124
00:05:49,909 --> 00:05:52,240
I will keep persuading my sister-in-law.

125
00:05:53,909 --> 00:05:55,000
But, Zhuzi's wife—

126
00:05:55,790 --> 00:05:59,350
even if our status and place
are different,

127
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:00,710
please believe me:

128
00:06:00,910 --> 00:06:02,640
my heart beats with yours.

129
00:06:03,150 --> 00:06:04,550
I want to use what little power I have

130
00:06:04,550 --> 00:06:06,790
to unite all of us farmers—

131
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,210
to stand together
and demand our rights from the landlords!

132
00:06:10,730 --> 00:06:11,790
Alright, alright.

133
00:06:11,790 --> 00:06:12,590
I believe you.

134
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,650
Now go on—keep persuading.

135
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:15,470
Go!

136
00:06:20,830 --> 00:06:22,430
This is indeed a stubborn ox.

137
00:06:25,970 --> 00:06:27,580
Here, all wrapped up for you.

138
00:06:28,150 --> 00:06:29,880
You're consuming this salt slow—

139
00:06:29,880 --> 00:06:31,350
better hurry before it clumps.

140
00:06:31,350 --> 00:06:33,010
Come back when it's finished.

141
00:06:34,790 --> 00:06:35,330
Humpback Guo!

142
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:36,470
What'd you throw at me?

143
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:37,470
Was that a dart?

144
00:06:37,520 --> 00:06:38,390
I'm here for treats!

145
00:06:38,390 --> 00:06:39,990
Get all your goodies out now!

146
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,520
You look rushed.

147
00:06:41,830 --> 00:06:43,520
Tell me then, what do you want?

148
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:45,159
My stock's running low...

149
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,370
That foreign candy

150
00:06:46,370 --> 00:06:47,620
that blackens teeth?

151
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:50,230
The...cho...chocolate?

152
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:52,140
Chocolate, dried persimmons,

153
00:06:52,210 --> 00:06:54,110
steamed dates, and sesame candy...

154
00:06:54,110 --> 00:06:56,010
Is this because of pregnancy cravings?

155
00:06:56,010 --> 00:06:57,909
Most people just
crave sour or spicy foods,

156
00:06:57,909 --> 00:06:59,110
but your cravings...

157
00:06:59,230 --> 00:07:00,230
quite a mixed bag!

158
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:02,510
I'm not in the mood for your jokes.

159
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:05,780
Who dared upset our precious miss?

160
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:07,650
My sister-in-law!

161
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:09,550
She went to the Goddess Temple without me.

162
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:11,870
Locked me home alone on such a fine day!

163
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:13,800
I'll do whatever I please now!

164
00:07:13,830 --> 00:07:15,420
See how well I know you?

165
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,520
I knew you were upset
the moment I saw you.

166
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,780
Good attitude though.

167
00:07:18,790 --> 00:07:20,000
If others treat us poorly,

168
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:22,080
no reason we should too, eh?

169
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,910
Wait here—let me get you some treats.

170
00:07:23,910 --> 00:07:25,030
Take your pick!

171
00:07:25,490 --> 00:07:26,830
But about that foreign candy...

172
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:28,780
We're fresh out of chocolate.

173
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:30,350
That shipment's always gone in a flash.

174
00:07:30,350 --> 00:07:31,080
No foreign candy?

175
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,150
Then why waste my time with all that talk?

176
00:07:33,150 --> 00:07:34,909
Now, young Miss, don't be angry—

177
00:07:34,909 --> 00:07:35,560
Look!

178
00:07:35,740 --> 00:07:37,890
These nut kernels are just as fine,

179
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:40,990
see?

180
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:42,730
And there's more—
a whole second layer underneath!

181
00:07:42,730 --> 00:07:44,909
Nothing new here—
we have all this at home.

182
00:07:44,909 --> 00:07:47,230
What nonsense! How's this not new?

183
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:48,830
Not a single tough bit in the batch—

184
00:07:48,830 --> 00:07:50,030
crispy as winter ice!

185
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,230
Wrap it all up.

186
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:00,320
Like all of it?

187
00:08:00,390 --> 00:08:02,120
Every last bit.
Put it on my account—

188
00:08:02,120 --> 00:08:04,050
just bill my sister-in-law later.

189
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:07,110
Wouldn't mind you
throwing more tantrums...

190
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,920
What was that?

191
00:08:11,080 --> 00:08:11,830
"I said...

192
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:14,080
your frown wounds my poor heart!

193
00:08:17,790 --> 00:08:19,010
Go home and wait for notice.

194
00:08:19,010 --> 00:08:20,870
We'll meet at Tietou's place later,

195
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:21,650
for the oath-taking.

196
00:08:21,650 --> 00:08:24,270
What's this Farmers' Association anyway?
And what's permanent tenancy?

197
00:08:24,270 --> 00:08:25,870
That's a very good question.

198
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,560
This Farmers' Association?
It's our salvation!

199
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,790
It's here to help folks like us—

200
00:08:31,270 --> 00:08:34,000
to stand with us farmers
and fight for our rights!

201
00:08:34,570 --> 00:08:35,860
We'll band together

202
00:08:35,890 --> 00:08:38,110
and demand permanent tenancy
from those landlords!

203
00:08:38,110 --> 00:08:39,640
What's permanent tenancy?

204
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:41,730
Permanent tenancy means that

205
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:43,880
we get to farm it forever.

206
00:08:44,230 --> 00:08:45,710
They can't just take it back
whenever they please,

207
00:08:45,710 --> 00:08:47,710
or hand it out to
whoever they like!

208
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:49,790
Now tell me—
is that good or what?

209
00:08:49,890 --> 00:08:50,560
Great!

210
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:54,350
What's drawn on this sign?

211
00:08:54,790 --> 00:08:55,820
A...mud eel?

212
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,400
Oh, that's no mud eel—

213
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,920
it's the emblem
of our Farmers' Association!

214
00:09:00,920 --> 00:09:04,200
What you're seeing is our plow—
the very tool that tills our soil!

215
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:04,930
Of course...

216
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:05,920
the carving on this sign

217
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:08,250
might not be the finest craftsmanship...

218
00:09:09,390 --> 00:09:10,050
Tietou.

219
00:09:11,680 --> 00:09:12,550
I planned to

220
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,230
finish mobilizing the masses

221
00:09:14,230 --> 00:09:15,400
before approaching you.

222
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:16,510
Because I knew—

223
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:17,760
with your influence,

224
00:09:17,780 --> 00:09:19,180
you could rally everyone

225
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:21,320
and get this Farmers' Association started
in no time.

226
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:22,630
But I never expected

227
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:24,440
you've already begun the work!

228
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:31,680
Here—take this.

229
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:34,420
These are my field notes

230
00:09:34,510 --> 00:09:35,500
from days of investigations.

231
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,170
I've already explained

232
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,930
the Association's purpose
to every farmer I met.

233
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,200
When you need help—

234
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,470
any help at all—
come find me.

235
00:09:42,470 --> 00:09:44,350
Whether practical groundwork
or theoretical guidance,

236
00:09:44,350 --> 00:09:45,870
I've got some experience to share.

237
00:09:45,870 --> 00:09:47,030
Go on, take them.

238
00:09:47,230 --> 00:09:48,200
Eyes off!

239
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:50,960
Mr. Fei.

240
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,750
What's this all about? I don't quite...

241
00:09:53,750 --> 00:09:54,750
I want to help you.

242
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:56,200
You—help me?

243
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:57,090
Oh, sure, sure.

244
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,200
This Farmers' Association—

245
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,040
it's the association for us farmers.

246
00:10:01,040 --> 00:10:02,280
What's it to you?

247
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:03,470
How could you help us?

248
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:04,600
Look at what you are.

249
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,280
A landlord's young master.

250
00:10:06,750 --> 00:10:08,070
A privileged son.

251
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,920
How can the Farmers' Association
tolerate a landload?

252
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:11,680
Answer me that!

253
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:13,200
-Exactly.
-That's true.

254
00:10:14,210 --> 00:10:16,010
So don't you go meddling in this!

255
00:10:16,110 --> 00:10:17,080
Alright, listen up everyone!

256
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,040
You few there—

257
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:19,200
listen up now:

258
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,320
Join the meeting at my place,

259
00:10:20,320 --> 00:10:21,200
and don't any of you forget it!

260
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:22,380
These are our own matters,

261
00:10:22,380 --> 00:10:23,510
so keep that in mind.

262
00:10:24,590 --> 00:10:25,800
Alright, break it up now, disperse!

263
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:27,230
Go about your business for now,
and wait for further notice!

264
00:10:27,230 --> 00:10:28,360
Wait for the notice!

265
00:10:28,920 --> 00:10:29,470
Okay.

266
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:30,750
Feng Tietou.

267
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:34,350
By order of Comrade Bai:

268
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:36,510
You are to attend the struggle session

269
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:37,800
against the despotic landlord Pan Xiaogui
in Xiazhuang Village this afternoon.

270
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,110
Bring your activist group

271
00:10:39,110 --> 00:10:39,800
to observe and learn from the proceedings.

272
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:40,800
A full debriefing meeting

273
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,560
will be convened upon his return.

274
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:44,080
Great news!

275
00:10:44,510 --> 00:10:45,380
That's great news!

276
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:47,060
Let's go now.

277
00:10:48,400 --> 00:10:49,230
Dajiao.

278
00:10:50,680 --> 00:10:51,230
Dajiao,

279
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:52,530
come on, keep up.

280
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:10,750
Mother.

281
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:14,040
I'm back from delivering Father's meal.

282
00:11:14,040 --> 00:11:16,530
He said he won't need
single-horned this afternoon.

283
00:11:16,530 --> 00:11:17,130
Come here.

284
00:11:17,960 --> 00:11:18,890
Where's Dajiao?

285
00:11:19,590 --> 00:11:20,590
He sent word

286
00:11:20,590 --> 00:11:23,540
that he's attending the struggle session
against Pan Xiaogui in Xiazhuang Village.

287
00:11:23,540 --> 00:11:24,600
He said not to worry

288
00:11:24,730 --> 00:11:26,920
and promised to return before nightfall.

289
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:27,280
Pass it to me.

290
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:27,830
Mother,

291
00:11:28,630 --> 00:11:29,990
I need to go out again.

292
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,040
Susu—

293
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:34,680
Susu.

294
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:38,410
Sister-in-law.

295
00:11:38,410 --> 00:11:39,340
Come here. Look!

296
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:41,200
